ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: In the past 3 months, how often have you been around a friend who was drinking in a manner or situation that worried you? Please take a moment to think about the past 3 months so you can select an accurate answer.
Notes: 0=0 times; 1=1-3 times (once a month or less); 2=4-6 times (once or twice a month); 3=7-9 times (two to three times a month); 4=10 or more times (more than three times a month); 9999=Missing data

ElementDescription: In the past 3 months, how many times have you done the following when you saw a friend who was drinking in a manner or situation that worried you? Made a plan to decrease the likelihood of your friends drinking too much (e.g., limited the amount of alcohol available, agreed to not have more than a certain number of drinks).
Notes: 0=0 times; 1=1-3 times (once a month or less); 2=4-6 times (once or twice a month); 3=7-9 times (two to three times a month); 4=10 or more times (more than three times a month); 9999=Missing data
